            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1380365988,
            "creation_date": 1380365988,
            "body": "<blockquote>\n  <p>I'm guessing the func wants an X amount of String variables, <\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>I guess you are looking for <strong>Varargs.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>Change your function signature to accept as <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public someReturnType func(String... vargs) { }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Which takes variable length of args as parameter.<\/p>\n\n<p>And then inside the method ,you can access them like <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>  for (String currentarg: args) {\n\n   // do something with currentarg\n } \n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>As a side note : Available from version 1.5 only.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/1.5.0/docs/guide/language/varargs.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Learn more from docs about Varargs<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 19066200,
            "question_id": 19066160
        }
